<br />

<br />
Over all very nicely done letter, I had to read the part about the fire pet twice though, at first it sounded like Why did it take so long to fix the fire pet, than re-read it and can see how you mean how long TO still fix the fire pet. I hope they know it is still broken. Though if they read this board, and play their game as they say, they will know, and should know.. humm why don't I ever see a level 50+ fire pet in use. Kind of a red flag.
<br />

<br />
The question how long till they answer the questions, and than how long to do something about them. I personally think a rushed answer won't be meaningful, so lets hope they take at least 2-3 hours to think it over, hash it out, nad give us valid answers that are well thought out.
<br />

<br />
Again Xal thank you for getting their attention, and sending a great letter to them. They have the message not only from the mage community but the game in general, and it will help. As for the opening about casuals versus ubers, was a great idea. SoE said that the majority of the player base is level 50 and below. You can not neglect such a large segment of the player population as they did in PoP and Gates and expect people to pay the bills for very long. By bringing it up at the start of the letter, you point out how important EQ is to all player at any level. A very important point, and it helps shows the concerns of this coommunity at least is for the mage class of all levels, and the game in general. Great job again.
<br />

<br />
Calebe
